Guys this is an exciting opportunity. Hotel Rangá is looking for a photographer to live with them for one month. Those of you that have followed me for awhile, know that this is one of my favourite hotels in Iceland. 

The job title is “It’s first official Northern Light Catcher”. As the job will include catching the beautiful lights in the environment of the hotel. As well as exploring all the magic of Iceland.

Please do me a favour and tag your photographer friends or favourite photographer to let them know about this opportunity 😄

Flights will be covered ✈️

Check out the link in stories to find out more information and apply! 😄

Good luck to you 🤞🏼@hotelranga

node.text:
Music video premiere, to the latest song by @musicbyragnar 🎵 : I’m at home. 

The best thing about travelling, is to get a bit of distance from the nature in Iceland. Because each time we come back, it feels like experiencing it for the first time all over again. 

The video portrays the journey from the airport back to Ragnars home farm in Hali, the cute yellow house that I have good memories from. The drive there is incredible, where you’ll pass waterfalls, glaciers and black sand beaches. I’m Ragnars mind, that drive always gives him the feeling that he’s finally home, so we wanted to capture that. 

I hope you enjoy and make sure to check out Ragnars music on Spotify and on his profile, for some more Icelandic music. 

😍❤️

I went on a super fun day-trip the other day. It’s a perfect itinerary from Reykjavík capital and in this video I share it with you.

Let me know in comments how you liked the video 😊

This area is often overlooked by travellers, but we can say that The Volcano has truly put it on the map in mix with the famous Blue Lagoon. 

Here’s my itinerary: 

Reykjavík - Krýsuvík - Kleifarvatn - Seltún - The Volcano - The Blue Lagoon - Reykjavík. 

Icelandair has great offers these days, for Iceland, volcano thirsty travellers 😄🌋 ✈️

#Iceland

node.text:
Sailing around the fjords of Iceland, scouting lines everyday and living on a yacht. We had a incredible days where we hiked and skied everyday, with nature as our bedroom, far away from civilisation. Together with the Aurora Arktika family. 

During that week we had seals swimming curiously around our boat, had untracked powder and did too many ocean swims to remember. 🌊

This week also makes you truly appreciate nature, disconnecting from the outside world and drop the phone and wifi.

Our bodies got so sore from all the hiking and skiing but it feels so good.

So who’s joining next trip?? 💁🏼‍♀️ 

Would love to hear your thoughts on the video below ❤️

Thank you for the good times @auroraarktika 

#Iceland​ #sailtoski​ #Westfjords

node.text:
I'm super excited to finally reveal this project with you. @Huaweimobile asked me to take their new phone, Mate 40 Pro, for a test around Iceland. I drove the full circle and captured my trip using only the phone. We had everything from beautiful winter conditions to extreme snow storms, just like you can expect from Iceland. As you'll see in the video I filmed frozen glacier lagoons, dog sledding, ski-touring, black beaches, and much much more. Along the way I tried a lot of fun features that Huawei has built into this phone (the super slow-mo being my favourite) and had a really good time shooting with it.

In this video you'll see my edit from the trip, followed by a summary of the phone and how I used it to shoot this film. I hope you like it and please let me know what you think!

#CapturedOnHuawei #HUAWEIMate40Pro #ad

....aaaand we're LIVE! Here's a little after-movie from our trip last summer 🚌

We were 25 new and old friends exploring Iceland together and for everyone involved this was one of our best weeks of the year. 

We road-tripped the full circle around Iceland during 7 days. We hiked volcanoes, found secret hot springs and sailed into the sunset on an old pirate ship.

Our website is now up and running and open for bookings 2021.
And the BEST part is that the trip is 100% refundable up until 10 days before the trip goes ahead in case of travel restrictions. 

I'm super excited to see you guys in Iceland! @vanlife_iceland

node.text:
I had so much fun, while spending a few days in the town of Vík. Located at the South Coast of Iceland. We spent these days exploring the beautiful area, the black beach but also decided to try two activities: ZipLining and Paragliding. With @ta_iceland and @ziplineiceland

The Zip-line ride was such a great adventure and is suitable for everyone. It was such a thrill gliding through the air, getting that adrenaline rush but also enjoying the beautiful surrounding nature. 

The Paragliding was one of my favorite activities I've ever done in Iceland. We managed to hang in the air, watch the Black beach below and surrounding glaciers. I really felt like a bird flying through the sky! 

Find the Paragliding here:
@ta_iceland 

Find the ZipLining here:
@ziplineiceland

node.title: Vlog: Paragliding and ZipLining in Iceland

node.text:
We sailed from Reykjavík to Húsavík, for the project; Set Sails for Sustainability. In this trip we’ve felt so connected to nature and our oceans. I feel lucky and proud to be a part of this amazing group of people that want to learn from each other, inspire and take action when it comes to our oceans. In this trip we’ve researched micro plastics in the waters and in fish, we’ve collected around 200kg of plastics and learnt about wildlife in the North Atlantic Ocean. I’ve also had the opportunity to do what I love the most, capture the experience in photos and video to use for awareness and bring you guys as well, partly on this journey.

I hope you enjoy this video from the trip, which captures the atmosphere pretty well. 
@oceanmissionsiceland @northsailing

Music by the wonderful @officialkaleo - I want more

node.text: Iceland’s festival weekend: “Verslunarmannahelgin”. Is a holiday weekend that is celebrated by the whole country, with multiple festivals scattered around the country. With the most famous one taking place at a small island, where a big part of the nation gathers together with bonfire, fireworks and dancing. Sadly the main one is cancelled this year, due to the situation. But my dearest @steffygunnars makes sure we still get to celebrate, by putting on her amazing evening-organising-skills and creating a whole weekend filled with same activities. Bonfire, concerts and dancing under the bright summer sky. 💃🏼☀️ #Iceland

Guys this is an exciting opportunity. Hotel Rangá is looking for a photographer to live with them for one month. Those of you that have followed me for awhile, know that this is one of my favourite hotels in Iceland. 

The job title is “It’s first official Northern Light Catcher”. As the job will include catching the beautiful lights in the environment of the hotel. As well as exploring all the magic of Iceland.

Please do me a favour and tag your photographer friends or favourite photographer to let them know about this opportunity 😄

Flights will be covered ✈️

Check out the link in stories to find out more information and apply! 😄

Good luck to you 🤞🏼@hotelranga

node.text:
Life in the bay 🐋 

It’s truly magical to be so close to these majestic animals. Have you ever been up close with a whale? 

I highly recommend adding whale watching in North Iceland to your Iceland itinerary.

#nature

node.text: We woke up to a rainy and cold day on the South Coast. So we were feeling lazy, had slept for long and out of energy 😆 Then we went for a little walk, found this beautiful waterfall and oasis and decided to go for a swim. I went first and then Leo couldn’t resist. We felt sooo much better afterwards and fully energised again. There is something seriously addictive about cold water swims 💦 #Iceland

So the secret is out: A mini Adventurer and a Van-lifer is joining us this Christmas 😄🚌 

We’re super excited about this new chapter in our life. I feel so lucky to have found Leo and how synced we are in so many ways. Until now we’ve done most of the things that were on our “Bucket list” and this felt like an awesome next step! 

So I’m 17weeks along and some of you have noticed a tiny bumps on my stories 😆, well spotted you! 

Anyway, the atmosphere around this feels very chilled for the both of us. Our goal the next couple of months is to enjoy the time we have left as “just the two of us”, with a goal of enjoying life and being free spirits 😄 

We’ve already started the process of adding “the third” seat to the Van 🚌 which is probably the most important preparation. 

Anyways, thank you for all your messages ❤️❤️ I’m so thankful for this loving community!!
